iption":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: unborn-HEAD behavior comes from real git command exit/status in an initialized repo with zero commits. MOCK-HIDE: stubs can normalize away the exact failure mode (fatal messages/exit codes) that causes real crashes. Rejected Integration due concrete behavior text: “repository that has no commits yet” is a real git state transition, best validated through actual subprocess + repo.","test_description":"Initialize a new git repo with no commits, run the CLI subprocess against it, assert successful execution and an empty structured report instead of traceback/error output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The counts in the report match the actual change history of the repository being analyzed.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this validates end-to-end correctness of history extraction plus categorization, across module handoff from git data source to report rendering. REAL-INFRA: requires real commit/change history semantics from git; in-process fakes risk asserting against the same mistaken assumptions as implementation. Rejected Integration because behavior text demands parity with “actual change history of the repository,” which is the system boundary.","test_description":"Construct a real repo history containing known added/deleted/renamed/modified events across several commits, execute CLI, and assert reported counts exactly match the known ground truth derived from the constructed history.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.89,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The output is identical whether the changes being analyzed are staged or unstaged.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: staged vs unstaged is git index/worktree behavior, which is OS/filesystem + git-state dependent. MOCK-HIDE: mocked repo responses can miss subtle divergences between index and working tree that appear only with real git operations. Rejected Integration because concrete behavior text compares two real git states (“staged or unstaged”) of repository changes.","test_description":"In a real repo, create equivalent changes and capture CLI output once with changes unstaged and once after staging; assert outputs are identical modulo allowed ordering/format determinism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.84,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}}]}
